<paragraph id="8BC378255605FFB8FF45FE53FEB9FD17" blockId="3.[151,1437,325,676]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
<emphasis id="B908A4375605FFB8FF45FE53FE22FE78" bold="true" box="[199,466,433,459]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Geographic variation.</emphasis>
This species, described by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFED05D45605FFB8FC95FE50FC21FE7F" author="Logunov, D. V." box="[791,977,434,460]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" pagination="59 - 66" refId="ref7819" refString="Logunov, D. V. (2001) New and poorly known species of the jumping spiders (Aranei: Salticidae) from Afghanistan, Iran and Crete. Arthropoda Selecta, 10 (1), 59 - 66." type="journal article" year="2001">Logunov (2001)</bibRefCitation>
from 
<collectingCountry id="F36B38B55605FFB8FB9FFE50FBBDFE7F" box="[1053,1101,434,460]" name="Iran" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Iran</collectingCountry>
, is here reported from 
<collectingCountry id="F36B38B55605FFB8FADEFE50FA69FE7F" box="[1372,1433,434,460]" name="India" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">India</collectingCountry>
. The male palps (
<figureCitation id="134764A05605FFB8FED4FE34FE28FE43" box="[342,472,470,496]" captionStart="FIGURES 14–18" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1942,1966]" captionTargetBox="[157,1408,706,1884]" captionTargetId="figure-194@3.[151,1435,700,1919]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 14–18. Stenaelurillus marusiki. 14 holotype, male, dorsal; 15, 17 male left palp, ventral view; 16 male left palp, retrolateral view; 18 male left palp, dorsal view. Photographed and figure prepared by Dmitri Logunov (Manchester Museum, UK)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6420423" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6420423/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Figs 14–18</figureCitation>
) are closely similar to those from 
<collectingCountry id="F36B38B55605FFB8FCE6FE34FC61FE43" box="[868,913,470,496]" name="Iran" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Iran</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFED05D45605FFB8FC23FE34FBBDFE43" author="Logunov, D. V." box="[929,1101,470,496]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" pagination="59 - 66" refId="ref7819" refString="Logunov, D. V. (2001) New and poorly known species of the jumping spiders (Aranei: Salticidae) from Afghanistan, Iran and Crete. Arthropoda Selecta, 10 (1), 59 - 66." type="journal article" year="2001">Logunov 2001</bibRefCitation>
), but the distal process in the Indian population appears to be somewhat more conical and slightly higher than embolus, while that of the Iranian population is rounder and about as high as embolus (
<figureCitation id="134764A05605FFB8FD75FDFCFC95FD8B" box="[759,869,542,568]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–13" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[179,1406,193,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-18@2.[179,1408,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–13. Stenaelurillus marusiki. 1, 6 male left palp, ventral view (NRC-AA-2067); 2, 7 same, retrolateral view; 3 embolus, dorsal view; 4, 8 epigyne, ventral view (NRC-AA-2072); 5, 9 vulva, dorsal view; 10 male, dorsal view; 11 same, ventral view; 12 female, dorsal view; 13 same, ventral view. Scale bars: 0.1 mm for genitalia and 1.0 mm for bodies." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6420421" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6420421/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Figs. 1, 3</figureCitation>
vs. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFED05D45605FFB8FC14FDFCFBCFFD8B" author="Logunov, D. V." box="[918,1087,542,568]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" pagination="59 - 66" refId="ref7819" refString="Logunov, D. V. (2001) New and poorly known species of the jumping spiders (Aranei: Salticidae) from Afghanistan, Iran and Crete. Arthropoda Selecta, 10 (1), 59 - 66." type="journal article" year="2001">Logunov 2001</bibRefCitation>
, fig. 29 and 
<figureCitation id="134764A05605FFB8FB50FDFCFAABFD8A" box="[1234,1371,542,569]" captionStart="FIGURES 14–18" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1942,1966]" captionTargetBox="[157,1408,706,1884]" captionTargetId="figure-194@3.[151,1435,700,1919]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 14–18. Stenaelurillus marusiki. 14 holotype, male, dorsal; 15, 17 male left palp, ventral view; 16 male left palp, retrolateral view; 18 male left palp, dorsal view. Photographed and figure prepared by Dmitri Logunov (Manchester Museum, UK)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6420423" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6420423/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Figs. 15–18</figureCitation>
). The white stripes on the carapace are more limited in the Indian population, narrow and reaching forward only to the PMEs, while those of Iranian males are wide and reach to a broad white area behind the AMEs (
<bibRefCitation id="EFED05D45605FFB8FB41FD84FA9CFD33" author="Logunov, D. V." box="[1219,1388,614,640]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" pagination="59 - 66" refId="ref7819" refString="Logunov, D. V. (2001) New and poorly known species of the jumping spiders (Aranei: Salticidae) from Afghanistan, Iran and Crete. Arthropoda Selecta, 10 (1), 59 - 66." type="journal article" year="2001">Logunov 2001</bibRefCitation>
, fig. 30 and 
<figureCitation id="134764A05605FFB8FF68FD68FECCFD17" box="[234,316,650,676]" captionStart="FIGURES 14–18" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1942,1966]" captionTargetBox="[157,1408,706,1884]" captionTargetId="figure-194@3.[151,1435,700,1919]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 14–18. Stenaelurillus marusiki. 14 holotype, male, dorsal; 15, 17 male left palp, ventral view; 16 male left palp, retrolateral view; 18 male left palp, dorsal view. Photographed and figure prepared by Dmitri Logunov (Manchester Museum, UK)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6420423" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6420423/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Fig. 14</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF0328AD5605FFB8FF15F874FF3BF844" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6420423" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6420423" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6420423/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" startId="3.[151,264,1942,1966]" targetBox="[157,1408,706,1884]" targetPageId="3">
<paragraph id="8BC378255605FFB8FF15F874FF3BF844" blockId="3.[151,1437,1942,2039]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
<emphasis id="B908A4375605FFB8FF15F874FEA6F81C" bold="true" box="[151,342,1942,1967]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">FIGURES 14–18.</emphasis>
<emphasis id="B908A4375605FFB8FEDCF875FDA3F81C" box="[350,595,1943,1967]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
<taxonomicName id="4C7C03A65605FFB8FEDCF875FDBFF81C" authorityName="Logunov" authorityYear="2001" box="[350,591,1943,1967]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Stenaelurillus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="marusiki">Stenaelurillus marusiki</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
<emphasis id="B908A4375605FFB8FDD8F875FD83F81C" bold="true" box="[602,627,1943,1967]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">14</emphasis>
holotype, male, dorsal; 
<emphasis id="B908A4375605FFB8FCF2F875FC40F81C" bold="true" box="[880,944,1943,1967]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">15, 17</emphasis>
male left palp, ventral view; 
<emphasis id="B908A4375605FFB8FB67F875FB0EF81C" bold="true" box="[1253,1278,1943,1967]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">16</emphasis>
male left palp, retrolateral view; 
<emphasis id="B908A4375605FFB8FECEF859FE95F860" bold="true" box="[332,357,1979,2003]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">18</emphasis>
male left palp, dorsal view. Photographed and figure prepared by Dmitri Logunov (Manchester Museum, UK).
</paragraph>
</caption>
<caption id="DF0328AD5602FFBFFF15FAC5FBB2FA8C" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6420425" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6420425" box="[151,1090,1319,1343]" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6420425/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" startId="4.[151,264,1319,1343]" targetBox="[154,1435,191,1295]" targetPageId="4">
<paragraph id="8BC378255602FFBFFF15FAC5FBB2FA8C" blockId="4.[151,1090,1319,1343]" box="[151,1090,1319,1343]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
<emphasis id="B908A4375602FFBFFF15FAC5FEA4FA8C" bold="true" box="[151,340,1319,1343]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">FIGURES 19–27.</emphasis>
<emphasis id="B908A4375602FFBFFED8FAC5FDBCFA8C" box="[346,588,1319,1343]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
<taxonomicName id="4C7C03A65602FFBFFED8FAC5FDB8FA8C" authorityName="Logunov" authorityYear="2001" box="[346,584,1319,1343]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Stenaelurillus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="marusiki">Stenaelurillus marusiki</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
habitus photographs. 
<emphasis id="B908A4375602FFBFFCAEFAC5FC9CFA8C" bold="true" box="[812,876,1319,1343]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">19–24</emphasis>
male; 
<emphasis id="B908A4375602FFBFFC32FAC5FC1FFA8C" bold="true" box="[944,1007,1319,1343]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">25–27</emphasis>
female.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8BC378255602FFBFFF45FA8FFBDAFA40" blockId="4.[151,1437,1389,2028]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
Although far from the Iranian 
<typeStatus id="54C7C6875602FFBFFDA4FA8CFDA6FA3B" box="[550,598,1390,1416]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">type</typeStatus>
locality, we recognize the Indian population as 
<taxonomicName id="4C7C03A65602FFBFFB02FA8CFAF0FA34" authorityName="Logunov" authorityYear="2001" box="[1152,1280,1389,1416]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Stenaelurillus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="marusiki">
<emphasis id="B908A4375602FFBFFB02FA8CFB7EFA3B" box="[1152,1166,1390,1416]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">S</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B908A4375602FFBFFB1CFA8FFAF0FA34" box="[1182,1280,1389,1415]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">marusiki</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in this study. The observed morphological differences between these two populations are slight, and variation in each population has not been thoroughly studied. However, a closer examination of morphology along with genetic evidence may eventually suggest otherwise, i.e., that these two populations are separate species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3662BAE5602FFBFFF45FA1FFDC6F9AB" box="[199,566,1533,1560]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BC378255602FFBFFF45FA1FFDC6F9AB" blockId="4.[151,1437,1389,2028]" box="[199,566,1533,1560]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
<emphasis id="B908A4375602FFBFFF45FA1FFECAF9A4" bold="true" box="[199,314,1533,1559]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. See 
<bibRefCitation id="EFED05D45602FFBFFEFAFA1CFDC1F9AB" author="Logunov, D. V." box="[376,561,1534,1560]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" pagination="59 - 66" refId="ref7819" refString="Logunov, D. V. (2001) New and poorly known species of the jumping spiders (Aranei: Salticidae) from Afghanistan, Iran and Crete. Arthropoda Selecta, 10 (1), 59 - 66." type="journal article" year="2001">Logunov (2001)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3662BAE5602FFBEFF45F9C3FD55FE3A" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BC378255602FFBFFF45F9C3FF15F8CC" blockId="4.[151,1437,1389,2028]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
<emphasis id="B908A4375602FFBFFF45F9C3FEA9F988" bold="true" box="[199,345,1569,1595]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Description.</emphasis>
<emphasis id="B908A4375602FFBFFEE4F9C3FE50F988" box="[358,416,1569,1595]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Male</emphasis>
(based on specimen NRC-AA-2067). Measurements: Carapace 1.99 long, 1.48 wide. Abdomen length 1.77, width 0.99. Leg measurements: I—2.40 (0.84, 0.41, 0.54, 0.34, 0.27); II—2.57 (0.91, 0.46, 0.50, 0.37, 0.33); III—4.50 (1.41, 0.67, 0.92, 1.11, 0.39); IV—4.50 (1.29, 0.56, 0.96, 1.19, 0.50). Leg formula III-IV-II-I. 
<emphasis id="B908A4375602FFBFFF6CF96FFEACF914" bold="true" box="[238,348,1677,1703]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Carapace</emphasis>
somewhat wider than abdomen. Anteriorly including ocular area black, covered with black scales and hairs, and brown medially. Two yellow longitudinal stripes running down behind PMEs. Two white bands along the lateral margins. 
<emphasis id="B908A4375602FFBFFEFAF937FE24F943" bold="true" box="[376,468,1749,1776]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Clypeus</emphasis>
brown, covered with yellow hairs. 
<emphasis id="B908A4375602FFBFFCE5F937FC13F943" bold="true" box="[871,995,1749,1776]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Chelicerae</emphasis>
vertical, narrow, brown. 
<emphasis id="B908A4375602FFBFFA80F937FAC7F943" bold="true" box="[1282,1335,1749,1776]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Palp</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="134764A05602FFBFFAC4F937FF0FF8A7" captionStart="FIGURES 1–13" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[179,1406,193,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-18@2.[179,1408,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–13. Stenaelurillus marusiki. 1, 6 male left palp, ventral view (NRC-AA-2067); 2, 7 same, retrolateral view; 3 embolus, dorsal view; 4, 8 epigyne, ventral view (NRC-AA-2072); 5, 9 vulva, dorsal view; 10 male, dorsal view; 11 same, ventral view; 12 female, dorsal view; 13 same, ventral view. Scale bars: 0.1 mm for genitalia and 1.0 mm for bodies." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6420421" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6420421/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Figs. 1, 2, 3, 6, 7</figureCitation>
): Cymbium yellowish. Embolus short. Distal projection conical, about as high as embolus. RTA slightly curved with blunt tip. 
<emphasis id="B908A4375602FFBFFE25F8FCFE2DF88B" bold="true" box="[423,477,1822,1848]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Legs</emphasis>
mostly yellow with some black, sparsely covered with black scales. Tarsi I black. 
<emphasis id="B908A4375602FFBFFF15F8A3FEF5F8EF" bold="true" box="[151,261,1857,1884]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Abdomen</emphasis>
with black median longitudinal band flanked by cream white stripes. Spinnerets yellow with dark brown apices.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC378255602FFBEFF45F86BFA9BFF4A" blockId="4.[151,1437,1389,2028]" lastBlockId="5.[151,1437,150,393]" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
<emphasis id="B908A4375602FFBFFF45F86BFEEBF810" box="[199,283,1929,1955]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Female</emphasis>
(based on specimen NRC-AA-2072). Measurements: Carapace 1.95 long, 1.55 wide. Abdomen length 3.44, width 2.40. Leg measurements: I—2.55 (0.89, 0.46, 0.54, 0.40, 0.26); II—2.84 (1.04, 0.55, 0.54, 0.39, 0.32); III—5.38 (1.69, 0.86, 1.12, 1.27, 0.44); IV—5.19 (1.54, 0.66, 1.07, 1.35, 0.57). Leg formula III-IV-II-I. 
<emphasis id="B908A4375602FFBFFA93F833FA8FF858" bold="true" box="[1297,1407,2001,2027]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Carapace</emphasis>
as in male. 
<emphasis id="B908A4375603FFBEFF74FF74FEA2FF02" bold="true" box="[246,338,150,177]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Clypeus</emphasis>
brown, sparsely covered with yellow hairs. 
<emphasis id="B908A4375603FFBEFCB5FF74FC43FF02" bold="true" box="[823,947,150,177]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Chelicerae</emphasis>
as in male. 
<emphasis id="B908A4375603FFBEFBB6FF75FB9AFF02" bold="true" box="[1076,1130,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Legs</emphasis>
as in males. 
<emphasis id="B908A4375603FFBEFB74FF74FA94FF02" bold="true" box="[1270,1380,150,177]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Abdomen</emphasis>
with central cream white longitudinal band flanked by black area. Laterally creamish-white. Spinnerets yellow. 
<emphasis id="B908A4375603FFBEFABFFF59FA6CFF66" bold="true" box="[1341,1436,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Epigyne</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="134764A05603FFBEFF1DFF3DFEB4FF4A" box="[159,324,222,249]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–13" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[179,1406,193,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-18@2.[179,1408,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–13. Stenaelurillus marusiki. 1, 6 male left palp, ventral view (NRC-AA-2067); 2, 7 same, retrolateral view; 3 embolus, dorsal view; 4, 8 epigyne, ventral view (NRC-AA-2072); 5, 9 vulva, dorsal view; 10 male, dorsal view; 11 same, ventral view; 12 female, dorsal view; 13 same, ventral view. Scale bars: 0.1 mm for genitalia and 1.0 mm for bodies." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6420421" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6420421/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Figs. 4, 5, 8, 9</figureCitation>
): ECP medially located on the triangular epigynal plate, deep, flanked by copulatory openings.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC378255603FFBEFF45FEE1FD55FE3A" blockId="5.[151,1437,150,393]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
<emphasis id="B908A4375603FFBEFF45FEE1FE75FEAF" bold="true" box="[199,389,258,285]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Natural history.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C7C03A65603FFBEFE09FEE1FD60FEAE" authorityName="Logunov" authorityYear="2001" box="[395,656,259,285]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Stenaelurillus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="marusiki">
<emphasis id="B908A4375603FFBEFE09FEE1FD60FEAE" box="[395,656,259,285]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Stenaelurillus marusiki</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
shares its habitat with 
<taxonomicName id="4C7C03A65603FFBEFC12FEE1FBF1FEAE" authority="Marathe &amp; Sanap &amp; Joglekar &amp; Caleb &amp; Maddison, 2022" authorityName="Marathe &amp; Sanap &amp; Joglekar &amp; Caleb &amp; Maddison" authorityYear="2022" box="[912,1025,259,285]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Stenaelurillus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vyaghri" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B908A4375603FFBEFC12FEE1FBF1FEAE" box="[912,1025,259,285]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">S. vyaghri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B908A4375603FFBEFB85FEE1FB91FEAE" bold="true" box="[1031,1121,259,285]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A23B194C5603FFBEFB85FEE1FB91FEAE" box="[1031,1121,259,285]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
in Sinnar, but 
<taxonomicName id="4C7C03A65603FFBEFA87FEE1FA73FEAE" authorityName="Logunov" authorityYear="2001" box="[1285,1411,259,285]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Stenaelurillus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="marusiki">
<emphasis id="B908A4375603FFBEFA87FEE1FA73FEAE" box="[1285,1411,259,285]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">S. marusiki</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is common during monsoon (July and August) while 
<taxonomicName id="4C7C03A65603FFBEFD4DFEC5FCB0FEF2" authority="Marathe &amp; Sanap &amp; Joglekar &amp; Caleb &amp; Maddison, 2022" authorityName="Marathe &amp; Sanap &amp; Joglekar &amp; Caleb &amp; Maddison" authorityYear="2022" box="[719,832,295,321]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Stenaelurillus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vyaghri" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B908A4375603FFBEFD4DFEC5FCB0FEF2" box="[719,832,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">S. vyaghri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B908A4375603FFBEFCC4FEC5FC50FEF2" bold="true" box="[838,928,295,321]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A23B194C5603FFBEFCC4FEC5FC50FEF2" box="[838,928,295,321]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
appears during late winter and continue to be active throughout the summer. The spiders were often observed moving actively around open small grass tufts, but occasionally were found beneath small bushes.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</treatment>
